    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures are shown. The first figure shows a string passing over a pulley. The left side of the string is attached to Block A, which has mass m sub A, and the right side of the string is attached to Block B, which has mass m sub B. Block A is smaller than Block B, and is slightly higher than Block B. The second figure shows two free body diagrams. The first diagram is labeled Block A and has two arrows extending from a dot. One arrow is of medium length and extends vertically upward, and one arrow is short and extends vertically downward. The second diagram is labeled Block B and has two arrows extending from a dot. One arrow is of medium length and extends vertically upward, and one arrow is long and extends vertically downward.\" src=\"/images/70a65d5b982b682155da42aa228d44c2.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">An Atwoodâ€™s machine consists of two blocks attached to a string that passes over a pulley, as shown. Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> and Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span> have masses of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub A\"><math alttext=\"m sub A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>A</mtext></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub B\"><math alttext=\"m sub B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>B</mtext></msub></math></span></span> respectively, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub A, is less than m sub B\"><math alttext=\"m sub A, is less than m sub B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>A</mtext></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>m</mi><mtext>B</mtext></msub></math></span></span>. The masses of the string and pulley are negligible, and the pulley can rotate with negligible friction around its axle. A student draws a free body diagram for each block, as shown. Which of the following is a correct statement regarding the accuracy of the free-body diagrams?</p>\n",
